---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Kite AI — Multi-provider AI chat. Bring your own keys."
  description="A calm, local-first AI chat client. Pick any provider (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, OpenRouter, Together, Groq), bring your own API key, and your conversations stay on your device."
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-background">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="relative pt-32 pb-20 px-6 overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-primary/5 via-transparent to-transparent pointer-events-none"></div>
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center relative z-10">
        <p class="text-primary font-medium tracking-wide uppercase text-sm mb-4">In closed beta</p>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold mb-6 text-text">
          kite ai
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed mb-4">
          One conversation. Every model.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-base max-w-xl mx-auto">
          A calm AI chat client that talks to whichever provider you already pay for. Your keys, your conversations, your device.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-10 flex items-center justify-center gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <a
            href="https://testflight.apple.com/join/XJ21v7RX"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg bg-primary text-white font-medium hover:opacity-90 transition"
          >
            Join the iOS beta
          </a>
          <a
            href="/kite-ai/privacy"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-white/10 text-text font-medium hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-white/[0.04] transition"
          >
            Privacy
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why -->
    <section class="py-16 px-6">
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-text mb-3">What's different</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-xl mx-auto">
            Most AI chat apps lock you in to one model and store your conversations on their servers. Kite AI does neither.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-white/[0.06] bg-white dark:bg-white/[0.03]">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-text mb-2">Bring your own key</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, OpenRouter, Together, Groq. Use the model you trust — switch mid-conversation if you don't like the answer.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-white/[0.06] bg-white dark:bg-white/[0.03]">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-text mb-2">Local first</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              Conversations live on your device in encrypted storage. Nothing routes through TinyKite servers.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-white/[0.06] bg-white dark:bg-white/[0.03]">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-text mb-2">Your repo, your history</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              Optional GitHub sync creates a private repo on your account. You own the data, you own the history. Disconnect anytime.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-white/[0.06] bg-white dark:bg-white/[0.03]">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-text mb-2">Calm interface</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              Monochrome, no clutter, no telemetry. A chat surface that gets out of the way.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Capabilities -->
    <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-white/[0.02]">
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-text mb-8 text-center">What you can do</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary">→</span>
            <span>Chat with any provider that supports the OpenAI or Anthropic API surface.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary">→</span>
            <span>Attach photos and ask vision-capable models about them.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary">→</span>
            <span>Voice dictation — speech-to-text runs entirely on your device.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary">→</span>
            <span>Per-chat custom system prompts and saved prompts you can reuse.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary">→</span>
            <span>Fork any message into a parallel exploration without losing the main thread.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary">→</span>
            <span>Optional sync to a private GitHub repo you own.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="py-20 px-6">
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-text mb-4">Try the beta</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
          iOS only for now. Android internal testing is coming via Play Store.
        </p>
        <a
          href="https://testflight.apple.com/join/XJ21v7RX"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg bg-primary text-white font-medium hover:opacity-90 transition"
        >
          Join the iOS beta on TestFlight
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
